      "content": "Grapefruit juice and atorvastatin are a combination that you should *not* mix, as it can cause your statin to build up in your system. This interaction can dangerously increase the side effects of the medication. For your safety, skip the juice with your breakfast and stick to water or a non-interacting beverage. Be sure to check with your pharmacist or doctor about your specific regimen.",
